cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.CR, cs.DS

The paper discusses a machine learning approach using probabilistic logic programs for generative-discriminative modeling. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of probabilistic context-free grammars (PCFG) and conditional random fields (CRF) also suggests a connection to natural language processing (cs.CL) and cryptography (cs.CR). Finally, the use of dynamic programming for efficient probability computation suggests a connection to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS).
